 <a href="/content/advanced-hard-drive-caching-techniques" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"><img src="http://www.linuxjournal.com/files/linuxjournal.com/ufiles/imagecache/teaser/nodeimage/story/harddrive_0.jpg" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-teaser" width="100" height="100" /></a> 
  
  


      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/advanced-hard-drive-caching-techniques" title="Advanced Hard Drive Caching Techniques">Advanced Hard Drive Caching Techniques</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/petros-koutoupis" title="View user profile.">Petros Koutoupis</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Nov 25, 2013 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_116 first"><a href="/tag/howtos" rel="tag" title="">HOWTOs</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_153"><a href="/tag/servers" rel="tag" title="">Servers</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_840"><a href="/tag/storage" rel="tag" title="">Storage</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_21 last active"><a href="/tag/sysadmin" rel="tag" title="" class="active">SysAdmin</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/advanced-hard-drive-caching-techniques" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        

<p>
With the introduction of the solid-state Flash drive, performance
came to the forefront for data storage technologies. Prior to that,
software developers and server administrators needed to devise methods
for which they could increase I/O throughput to storage, most of which
resulted in low capacity caching to random access memory (RAM)
or a RAM drive.<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/advanced-hard-drive-caching-techniques"> more>></a></span></p>
  </div>



  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_comments first last"><a href="/content/advanced-hard-drive-caching-techniques#comments" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">4 comments</a></li>
</ul>
