      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/manage-your-configs-vcsh" title="Manage Your Configs with vcsh">Manage Your Configs with vcsh</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/bill-childers" title="View user profile.">Bill Childers</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Nov 19, 2013 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_300 first"><a href="/tag/configuration-management" rel="tag" title="">Configuration Management</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_116"><a href="/tag/howtos" rel="tag" title="">HOWTOs</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_21 last active"><a href="/tag/sysadmin" rel="tag" title="" class="active">SysAdmin</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/manage-your-configs-vcsh" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        

<p>
If you're anything like me (and don't you want to be?), you probably have more
than one Linux or UNIX machine that you use on a regular basis. Perhaps
you've got a laptop and a desktop. Or, maybe you've got a few servers on which
you have
shell accounts.<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/manage-your-configs-vcsh"> more>></a></span></p>
